Subdivision.SubDescription: St. James Park is an all-encompassing lifestyle that you will be proud to be a part of. It is seemingly tucked away while conveniently located near the bustling shopping, dining and commercial sectors of Norman. With acres of rolling fields, tranquil ponds and walking paths, St. James Park pairs a comfortable environment with exquisite custom homes and optimal amenities. It’s more than a neighborhood, it’s a lifestyle. St. James Park has an outdoor experience for you. Sitting on more than 200 acres, our community boasts miles of walking paths, 3 large tranquil ponds, and a full basketball court. Our welcoming clubhouse is a gathering place for neighborhood meetings and can be utilized by members of our community for private events such as family reunions and birthday parties. The clubhouse features a modern kitchen, dining room, and fireplace, as well as an Exercise Center equipped with Life Fitness equipment. Lounge with your favorite book, take a refreshing dip, or swim laps. Our swimming pool is conveniently located at the center of the neighborhood, where community members are invited to relax poolside in one of the many deck chairs or splash around in the 50-foot pool. St. James Park is located in the highly praised Norman Public School District. This neighborhood is served by: Reagan Elementary School, Washington Irving Middle School, Norman High School.

Vintage Creek community, perfectly located in Norman, OK, with prices starting in the $320's. Conveniently located less than 2 miles east of I-35 on Tecumseh Road, the Vintage Creek community sits on Norman’s Legacy Trail as its newest Community. Take a walk or a bike ride with your loved ones on the beautiful Legacy Trail to the Legacy Park area, home of some of the best food and shopping that Norman has to offer. In Vintage Creek, you can have it all: a beautiful home, a beautiful community, great amenities, and an unbeatable lifestyle. Come and enjoy the neighborhood pool, walking trail and so much more!

- Homes Starting at 2,400 SQFT (Section 3)
Neighborhood Amenities: - Gated Community - Pool - Clubhouse - Stocked Ponds (Catch and Release) - Basketball Court - Playground - HOA Cost $640 per Year
Moore Public Schools: - Oakridge - Southridge - South Moore

Sendera Lakes is the premier community in Southwest Moore and located in the Moore School District. Our community is located at the Southeast corner of SW 34 (SW164 in OKC) and Santa Fe, this premier community offers large homesites with beautiful lake sites available as well. Our swimming pool and luxury Community Center will be completed soon and is located in the center of the neighborhood. When you live in Sendera you will find the convenience of your 2 minute drive to all the wonderful shopping and food experiences that Moore has to offer.

Mustang Park is a brand new, luxury family living in Mustang, Oklahoma! Features include a large green belt, community pool, basketball court, soccer field and fitness center. Its close proximity to the Turnpike also makes commuting a breeze, and community events, parties, and activities are offered. For children's safety, Mustang Park offers a private walking path from the community to the local elementary and middle school. Reserve your homesite today!

Just off the beaten path, 10 minutes south of Norman, lies an emerging acres community in the heart of the countryside: Chapel Acres. Recently named by Niche in 2018 as the #2 Best Place to Buy a House in Oklahoma, Goldsby is one of the state's best kept secrets...but not for long. With stunning hilltop views of the OU stadium and downtown OKC, your oasis awaits you. Why buy just a house in any neighborhood when you can dial down the pace and create your dream lifestyle in the wide-open air of Oklahoma? Count the stars at night, have the best view of the city lights, and rest easy knowing your family can safely play outside. At the heart of our community, the neighbors of Chapel Acres gather at The Chapel. Our gorgeous main event center was holistically designed for community wide gatherings, celebrations, events, meetings, or simply a spontaneous hangout with friends and family. Our outdoor common area features an impressive Basketball Court, Bocce Ball Court, and lavish Pavilion complete with an outdoor Kitchen and Picnic Area while our 6,000 square foot luxurious clubhouse comes fully equipped with an indoor game room, family gym, toddler area, comfortable seating, and a fully functional event space with a catering kitchen making The Chapel your go-to space for gatherings of every kind.

Subdivision.SubDescription: Welcome to Las Colinas and Fountain View, two of West Norman’s newest and most prestigious communities. Nestled on the west side of Norman (off of 48th and Techumseh), Las Colinas and Fountain View are both exciting, upscale communities with inviting water featured entrances and gorgeous sunset views. Landscaped among fabulous home sites, these communities offer oversized sites as well. Enjoy this convenient location close to Brookhaven Village, highways, shopping opportunities, restaurants, and the Norman Health Plex. These amazing communities are served by the highly acclaimed Norman school district, ranked among the finest school districts in the state. Community amenities include high-end custom design features and selections, beautiful elevations with tall roof lines, and gorgeous stone. Embrace our distinctive, unique style that sets us apart from all other builders out there, with the help of our award-winning professional designer to be used throughout the entire building process. Take advantage of our Brookfield Custom Homes Designer and Custom Plan Drawing Team to help make the vision of your new home come to life!
